          <div id="profile-settings">
            <h3>Profile Settings</h3>
            <p>
              <strong>hackrLog()</strong> has a few settings that affect the way you work. When logged in you can
              view your Profile Settings by clicking the <strong>Profile</strong> link in the page header.
            </p>
            <ul class="thumbnails">
              <li>
                <div class="thumbnail">
                  <%= image_tag "settings.png" %>
                  <div class="caption"><p>View or update your Profile Settings.</p></div>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              From this form you can update your e-mail address, nickname, timezone, syntax highlighting style and
              whether or not your last used tags are saved for new entries.
            </p>
            <h4>E-Mail Address</h4>
            <p>
              The e-mail provided here serves as your account identifier and will also be used to communicate with
              you regarding any changes in your account status.
            </p>
            <h4>Nickname</h4>
            <p>
              The nickname is simply for display purposes and does not need to be unique. You will see it in the
              page title when logged in.
            </p>
            <h4>Timezone</h4>
            <p>
              The timezone is used to adjust the creation and update times for your entries. Entries are shown with
              an approximate time since creation. Setting your timezone will ensure that the time value will be correct.
            </p>
            <h4>Save Tags</h4>
            <p>
              This setting, when turned on, will reuse the last set of tags for your next entry. If you typically
              create many entries that are related to each other this can save you the hassle of re-typing the
              tags for each entry. When turned off you must enter the tags manually for each entry.
            </p>
            <h4>Syntax Highlighting Style</h4>
            <p>
              This drop down provides a list of syntax highlighting color styles. Select a color style and code blocks
              in entries will display with the selected color styles.
            </p>
            <h4>Additional Profile Options</h4>
            <p>
              If you have a Gravatar account you will see your primary Gravatar image on the profile page. There is
              also a link to the Gravatar site if you wish to create an account or update your existing account.
            </p>
            <p>
              You can change your account password by clicking the <strong>Password</strong> tab and providing your
              existing password and the new password.
            </p>
            <p>
              Upgrading to <strong>hackrLog() Premium</strong> can be accomplished by clicking the <strong>Go Premium</strong>
              tab and entering your credit card information.
            </p>
            <p>
              You can export your entry data at any time by clicking the <strong>Export Data</strong> tab. Select the
              desired export format and then click the <strong>Export</strong> button. Your data will be downloaded to
              your machine in a Zip file.
            </p>
            <p>
              If you wish to cancel your account click the <strong>Cancel Account</strong> tab. Check the cancel
              account checkbox, supply your account password and click the <strong>Cancel</strong> button. Your account
              will be closed, all data removed from <strong>hackrLog()</strong> and any recurring credit card charges will
              be stopped.
            </p>
            <a href="#help">top</a>
          </div><br/>
          <div id="keyboard-interface">
            <h3>Keyboard Interface</h3>
            <p>
              <strong>hackrLog()</strong> provides a keyboard interface for working with entries to make entering, editing
              and deleting entries easy. While the <strong>Log Entry</strong> or <strong>Tags</strong> fields have focus
              the keys shown below will not trigger the corresponding actions.
            </p>
            <table class="table table-bordered table-striped">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Key</th>
                  <th>Action</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td class="key">
                    <p>n</p>
                  </td>
                  <td>
                    <p>Create a new entry. This moves the cursor to the <strong>Log Entry</strong> field in preparation for a new entry.</p>
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>
                    <p>j</p>
                  </td>
                  <td>
                    <p>Select the next item in the entry list. Repeatedly pressing the j key will continue moving down the entry list. The selected entry is shown with a blue left border highlight and a darker background.</p>
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>
                    <p>k</p>
                  </td>
                  <td>
                    <p>Select the previous item in the entry list. Repeatedly pressing the k key will continue moving up the entry list. The selected entry is shown with a blue left border highlight and a darker background.</p>
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>
                    <p>e</p>
                  </td>
                  <td>
                    <p>Edit the selected entry. This is the same as clicking the <strong>Edit</strong> link for an entry.</p>
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>
                    <p>d</p>
                  </td>
                  <td>
                    <p>Delete the selected entry. This is the same as clicking the <strong>Delete</strong> link for an entry.</p>
                  </td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
            <p>
              Another way of selecting an entry is to hover the mouse over it. You can mouse over and entry and still use the <em>e</em>
              and <em>d</em> keys to edit or delete the selected entry.
            </p>
            <a href="#help">top</a>
          </div>
